## Review Package Assembly

Before any agent runs, the worker assembles a structured **Review Package** from the raw
PR data. This is done in `RunReviewPipelineUseCase` and stored in `ReviewState`.

### Structure

```
ReviewPackage
├── pr_metadata
│   ├── title, description, author
│   ├── base_sha, head_sha, base_branch, head_branch
│   └── changed_files: list[{path, status: added|modified|deleted, additions, deletions}]
│
├── context_units: list[ContextUnit]       ← one per function/class containing ≥1 changed line
│   ├── file_path
│   ├── node_type: "function" | "class" | "module"
│   ├── node_name
│   ├── start_line, end_line
│   ├── body_old: str                      ← complete old version (from base_sha)
│   ├── body_new: str                      ← complete new version (from head_sha)
│   └── diff_patch: str                    ← unified diff for this unit only
│
└── rag_chunks: dict[AgentType, list[CodeChunk]]   ← populated per-agent before its run
    ├── security → top-5 auth/crypto/input-handling functions
    ├── perf     → top-5 DB/loop/IO functions
    ├── arch     → top-5 import/class-hierarchy chunks
    └── test     → top-5 test files related to changed modules
```

### Assembly Pipeline

```
1. Fetch raw diff from GitHub (base_sha → head_sha)
2. For each changed file:
   a. Fetch new file content (head_sha)
   b. Fetch old file content (base_sha) — skip for added files
   c. Parse both with tree-sitter → extract function/class nodes
   d. Identify which nodes contain ≥1 changed line (by line range intersection)
   e. Build ContextUnit: body_old, body_new, diff_patch for that node
3. Embed all new file content → store in code_embeddings (if not already for this SHA)
4. SupervisorAgent reads context_units metadata (file types, node names) → decides active agents
5. Before each specialist agent runs → query pgvector with agent-specific query → populate rag_chunks
```

### Large Function Handling

Functions >300 lines are trimmed to preserve the context budget:
```
signature + first 30 lines
...
[N changed lines ± 10 lines of surrounding context]
...
last 5 lines before return statement
```

### Large PR Handling (>50 changed files)

Split context_units into batches of 10 files. Each agent is called once per batch.
SynthesisAgent receives all batch findings and deduplicates across batches.

### Embedding Cleanup

On `pull_request.closed` webhook:
```sql
DELETE FROM code_embeddings
WHERE repository_id = $repo_id AND commit_sha = $head_sha
```
Weekly background cleanup removes rows older than 30 days as a safety net.
